 returned empty text for heartbeat-state.json, and the corpus=\\\"memory\\\" didn't work. Let me check the workspace file directly.\\n\\nLooking at the sessions list, I can see many sessions. Let me compare the current state vs what I know from the last report (23:41 UTC).\\n\\nFrom the last report at 23:41 UTC, the active sessions were:\\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` (5p QLHV monitor) ‚Äî running ‚úÖ\\n- `cron:6f3323ef` (5p DTLX monitor) ‚Äî running ‚úÖ \\n- `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status to Lead) ‚Äî running ‚úÖ\\n\\n\\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` ‚Äî running ‚úÖ\\n\\nNow looking at 23:54 UTC, I'm tracking the same cron jobs and Telegram sessions, but I notice some of the historical entries show as \\\"done\\\" even though they're marked as running. Let me cross-reference the main cron session to get a clearer picture of what's actually active right now.\\n\\nThe DTLX monitor has been running for about 3 hours since its last update, the QLHV monitor is also active, and there's a status report that went out to the Lead around 22:05. I need to read the heartbeat-state.json file directly to see the full picture of what's actually running.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_q4my0vuzjw38_1\",\n              \"name\": \"read\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"path\": \"heartbeat-state.json\"\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 29033,\n            \"output\": 308,\n            \"totalTokens\": 43694,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13944,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 409,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776210879446,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e06c09270b958b352290b32b81b23\",\n          \