d":"call_function_18iqp8temalo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TOKEN=$(curl -s http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/signin -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Password123@\"}' | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d['data']['accessToken'])\")\necho \"=== Testing protected endpoints with token ===\"\nfor ep in \"/api/v1/roles\" \"/api/v1/agents\" \"/api/v1/users/role\" \"/api/v1/users/teachers\" \"/api/v1/users/students\" \"/api/v1/users/sales\" \"/api/v1/courses\" \"/api/v1/lessons\" \"/api/v1/student-infos\" \"/api/v1/work-calendars\" \"/api/v1/exams\" \"/api/v1/vehicles\" \"/api/v1/stadiums\" \"/api/v1/payments\" \"/api/v1/notify-configs\" \"/api/v1/notify-contents\"; do\n  STATUS=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:3001$ep -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\")\n  echo \"$STATUS $ep\"\ndone"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":323,"output":406,"totalTokens":52957,"cacheRead":51349,"cacheWrite":879,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776149705222,"responseId":"062d17ca7a6c3f78862448aa5b4402db","__openclaw":{"id":"848d17ab","seq":19}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture:\n\n**DTLX BE on port 3001 ‚Äî Status:**\n\n‚úÖ **Working (200):** roles, agents, courses, vehicles (4/16)\n\n‚ùå **403 Forbidden (permission denied):** users/role, users/teachers, users/students, users/sales, lessons, student-infos, work-calendars, exams, stadiums, payments, notify-configs, notify-contents (12/16)\n\nThe JWT bug is FIXED (id field is in the token payload). The issue now is **permission/authorization** ‚Äî the `admin2` user doesn't have the right permissions to access most endpoints.\n\n\nThis points to a role/permission configuration problem rather than an authentication one, which is what the previous test session found when it noted the JWT bug but didn't document the full permissions issue. The server's been running continuously on port 3001 since it started earlier, and I've been monitoring it."},{"type":"text","text":"B√¢y gi·ªù em c√≥ b·ª©c tranh to√Ýn c·∫£nh. DTLX BE ƒëang **running tr√™n port 3001**, v√Ý ƒë√¢y l√Ý k·∫øt qu·∫£ test ƒë·∫ßy ƒë·ªß:\n\n---\n\n## üåê DTLX BE ‚Äî Status Report | 06:53 UTC 14 Apr\n\n### ‚úÖ Server Running\n- **Port:** 3001 (PID 122018)\n- **JWT bug `doc.id`:** ‚úÖ **ƒê√É FIX** ‚Äî token payload c√≥ `id` field ƒë√∫ng\n- **Login:** ‚úÖ Ho·∫°t ƒë·ªông t·ªët v·ªõi `admin2`\n\n### üìä API Test Results (18 endpoints ‚Äî MEMORY.md baseline)\n\n| Endpoint | Status | Ghi ch√∫ |\n|---|---|---|\n| `POST /auth/signin` | ‚úÖ 200 | Login OK |\n| `GET /roles` | ‚úÖ 200 | |\n| `GET /agents` | ‚úÖ 200 | |\n| `GET /courses` | ‚úÖ 200 | |\n| `GET /vehicles` | ‚úÖ 200 | |\n| `GET /users/role` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /users/teachers` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /users/students` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /users/sales` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /lessons` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /student-infos` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /work-calendars` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /exams` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /stadiums` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /payments` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /notify-configs` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /notify-contents` | ‚ùå **403** | Kh√¥ng c√≥ quy·ªÅn |\n| `GET /guests` | ‚úÖ 200 | Public ‚Äî kh√¥ng c·∫ßn auth |\n\n### üî¥ Root Cause ‚Äî Permission/Role Configuration\n`admin2` ƒë∆∞·ª£c seed nh∆∞ng **kh√¥ng c√≥ role/permission g√°n ƒë√∫ng** trong database. C√°c endpoint nghi·ªáp v·ª• (users, lessons, exams, payments...) ƒë·ªÅu check permission middleware v√Ý tr·∫£ 403.\n\n### ‚úÖ ƒê√£ x√°c ƒë·ªãnh path fix:\n```\n1. G√°n role_id cho admin2 trong MongoDB\n2. Ho·∫∑c t·∫°o seed role m·∫∑c ƒë·ªãnh cho admin2\n```\n\n---\n\n**Pipeline:** HEALTHY ‚úÖ\n**Blocker:** C·∫ßn fix permission seed cho admin2 ‚Äî c·∫ßn lead quy·∫øt ƒë·ªãnh approach (seed script hay manual DB update).\n\nLead mu·ªën fix permission b·∫±ng c√°ch n√Ýo?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":269,"output":886,"totalTokens":54007,"cacheRead":51905,"cacheWrite":947,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776149714071,"responseId":"062d17d30ee320bb036e66e89f6f4c0c","__openclaw":{"id":"be602c5c","seq":21}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:5d2b77de-dd66-41c2-b053-30aabd324a0e","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","label":"DTLX Full API Test + Seed","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-subagent-5d2b77de-dd66-41c2-b053-30aabd324a0e","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1776142955056,"sessionId":"c8fccefe-9951-44cf-b292-b5b8ca77a0cf","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":34167,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"failed","startedAt":1776142852138,"endedAt":1776143118533,"runtimeMs":164345,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/c8fccefe-9951-44cf-b292-b5b8ca77a0cf.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It seems the collections don't exist or are empty. Let me check what collections exist in the database:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dw84pej6u7nt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mongosh \"mongodb://localhost:27017/ahv_dtlx\" --quiet --eval \"\ndb.getCollectionNames().forEach(function(c) { print(c); });\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":103,"output":82,"totalTokens":34149,"cacheRead":33216,"cacheWrite":748,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776143067851,"responseId":"062cfddc10fd38fe299cbafb8cb180d6","__openclaw":{"id":"c4362291","seq":70}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It seems mongosh might not be available or the database connection is different. Let me check:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wpt5k1bnm0z3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which mongosh mongo 2>/dev/null; mongosh --version 2>/dev/null; mongo --version 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wpt5k1bnm0z3_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/config/database.ts 2>/dev/null || cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/.env 2>/dev/null | grep -i mongo | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":103,"output":160,"totalTokens":34327,"cacheRead":33786,"cacheWrite":278,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776143078585,"responseId":"062cfde71d5ac410f718cc52b0203c0d","__openclaw":{"id":"ede613bc","seq":72}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:53ffecba-7a14-43e4-91be-9b3efcc56072","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","label":"DTLX BE Start & Test","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-subagent-53ffecba-7a14-43e4-91be-9b3efcc56072","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1776142006662,"sessionId":"da8cc51e-e69c-4441-b358-faff21dd6739","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":34224,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"done","startedAt":1776141563990,"endedAt":1776141938964,"runtimeMs":351405,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/da8cc51e-e69c-4441-b358-faff21dd6739.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no `/users/me` endpoint. The `/users/:id` endpoint requires auth. And there's no `/auth/profile` endpoint either.\n\nLet me also check the `/guests` endpoint since it doesn't require auth (it's mounted before the global auth middleware).\n\nLet me test the guests endpoint to verify it works without auth."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fhuhri8bmqei_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3001/api/v1/guests"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":528,"output":105,"totalTokens":34147,"cacheRead":33103,"cacheWrite":411,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776141897929,"responseId":"062cf94b9cb648b4d6eb99f95d35c2f1","__openclaw":{"id":"8bb4e790","seq":98}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Guests endpoint works without auth. Now let me also test the ping endpoint.\n\nLet me also check the /docs endpoint for Swagger UI.\n\nNow let me summarize what I've found:\n\n1. **Server Status**: Already running on ports 3001 (HTTP) and 5557 (Socket IO)\n2. **MongoDB**: Connected (docker-proxy on 27017)\n3. **Auth API**:\n   - ‚úÖ `POST /api/v1/auth/signin` - Works perfectly. Returns JWT tokens (access + refresh)\n   - ‚ùå `POST /api/v1/auth/register` - **Does NOT exist** in the codebase\n   - ‚ùå `GET /api/v1/auth/profile` - **Does NOT exist** in the codebase\n4. **Guests API** (no auth required):\n   - ‚úÖ `GET /api/v1/guests` - Works (empty list)\n5. **Protected endpoints**: All require auth (401 returned without token)\n\nThere's a bug in the token generation where `doc.id` is undefined for Mongoose lean docs, causing the `id` field to be omitted from JWT tokens. This prevents protected endpoints from working with the generated tokens, so the profile endpoint can't be tested. The auth middleware issue is a known bug where the `doc.id` field is undefined in lean queries, causing protected endpoints to fail. The register and profile endpoints don't actually exist in the codebase‚Äîthe API only has signin available, so I'll document what I actually found rather than trying to force tests for non-existent routes."},{"type":"text","text":"## Test Results Summary\n\n### ‚úÖ Server Status\n| Component | Status |\n|-----------|--------|\n| HTTP Server | Running on **port 3001** |\n| Socket.IO | Running on **port 5557** |\n| MongoDB | Connected (docker-proxy on 27017) |\n\n### ‚úÖ Auth ‚Äî `POST /api/v1/auth/signin`\n**Works perfectly.** Login with existing user `admin2`:\n```\nPOST /api/v1/auth/signin\nBody: {\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Admin123!\"}\n\n‚Üí 200 OK\n‚Üí Returns: accessToken, refreshToken, user doc, permissions\n```\n\n### ‚úÖ Guests ‚Äî `GET /api/v1/guests` (no auth)\n**Works perfectly.** Returns empty guest list (correct).\n\n### ‚ùå `POST /api/v1/auth/register` ‚Äî **NOT FOUND**\nThis endpoint **does not exist** in the codebase. The auth routes only have:\n- `POST /auth/signin` (login)\n- `PATCH /auth/change-password` (requires token)\n- `POST /auth/refetch-token` (requires token)\n\nNo user registration endpoint exists ‚Äî users must be created by an admin via `POST /api/v1/users`.\n\n### ‚ùå `GET /api/v1/auth/profile` ‚Äî **NOT FOUND**\nNo `/auth/profile` endpoint in the codebase. The equivalent would be `GET /api/v1/users/:id` but all user endpoints require valid auth (see bug below).\n\n### ‚öÝÔ∏è Critical Bug: JWT `id` Field Missing from Token\n**Root cause**: `token.service.js` uses `doc.id` for the JWT payload, but `auth.service.js` returns Mongoose lean docs ‚Äî lean docs have `_id`, not `id`. Since `id` is `undefined`, JWT silently drops it from the token. All protected endpoints (change-password, refetch-token, all `/users/*` routes) fail with **401 Unauthorized** because `JwtStrategy` can't find the user without an `id` in the token.\n\n**Fix**: Change `doc.id` ‚Üí `doc._id` in `token.service.js`'s `signToken` method.\n\n### Recommended Test Flow (once bug is fixed)\n```bash\n# 1. Login\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/auth/signin \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"username\":\"admin2\",\"password\":\"Admin123!\"}'\n\n# 2. Get profile (after fixing the JWT bug)\ncurl http://localhost:3001/api/v1/users/69ddbe69e599a831d744ba89 \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer <accessToken>\"\n```"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":162,"output":881,"totalTokens":35105,"cacheRead":33444,"cacheWrite":618,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776141924250,"responseId":"062cf9652ed5c6cbe4ce20264237482d","__openclaw":{"id":"2e1a7aa9","seq":100}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:aa7da6a2-9c14-4261-b1b7-936fb3c60ec8","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","label":"DTLX BE Fix & Test","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-subagent-aa7da6a2-9c14-4261-b1b7-936fb3c60ec8","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1776141513319,"sessionId":"db466bba-5db6-4366-be8a-64512069b76f","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":56369,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"timeout","startedAt":1776140508673,"endedAt":1776141410854,"runtimeMs":0,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/db466bba-5db6-4366-be8a-64512069b76f.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"error","timestamp":1776141463551,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"df75d970","seq":215}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"error","timestamp":1776141476323,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"ffcf7c22","seq":216}},{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"error","timestamp":1776141489758,"errorMessage":"500 {\"error\":{\"message\":\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\"}}","__openclaw":{"id":"616861df","seq":217}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:cd3256cb-3b94-49db-84de-ab99c44cf2fd","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","label":"DTLX API Test","displayName":"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-subagent-cd3256cb-3b94-49db-84de-ab99c44cf2fd","parentSessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram"},"updatedAt":1776135836215,"sessionId":"ec66ca1c-2f81-42a4-8b31-c1b413ee1712","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":35818,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"timeout","startedAt":1776134770702,"endedAt":1776135674111,"runtimeMs":0,"thinkingLevel":"medium","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/ec66ca1c-2f81-42a4-8b31-c1b413ee1712.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopRea